4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists even without any prior knowledge. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills in securing these environments.

Participants will learn about cloud security, offensive and defensive penetration testing, and cyber threat intelligence analysis. They will also gain proficiency in managing risks through data loss prevention strategies and compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST.

The bootcamp is 16 weeks long and includes three live online classes per week. Class sizes are kept small, with up to 16 people, to ensure personalized attention. Upon completion, participants will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions.

This program is suitable for individuals with no previous experience in cybersecurity.

For more information, visit: https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity.

